1
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:20,867
Wait, why did you bring me here?

2
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,567
This is where we'll do
community service?

3
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:23,800
Yes.

4
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:26,100
We're going to pick sunflowers

5
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:28,367
because there will be an event
later in the city hall.

6
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,233
There's a cooking contest.

7
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,667
It's sponsored by the LGU.

8
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:34,200
So technically,
this is your community service.

9
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:37,167
Wait, is Grandmother Ikay
included in the cooking contest?

10
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:42,633
Hey, good thing you arrived.

11
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,300
I have supporters now.

12
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:47,233
I've been so nervous.

13
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:49,100
Grandmother Ikay, you can do it.

14
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:51,500
Your pinangat
is already a winner.

15
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:55,100
Who would not be jealous?

16
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:58,100
Your dimples attract women.

17
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,300
You, too.

18
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:02,800
You know Tiffany, I fell in love
with that dimples of yours.

19
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,667
It's just a freaking show,
James.

20
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:07,567
For me, it's not.

21
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:09,200
This is not a show.

22
00:01:09,267 --> 00:01:10,167
You like him.

23
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,533
Do you see your girlfriend
as a flirt?

24
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:15,000
If that's the case,
we should break up...

25
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,867
because it's embarrassing
for you.

26
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:20,100
You're a very good person
and your girlfriend is a flirt.

27
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:21,567
Grandmother Ikay!

28
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:22,967
There's nobody there.

29
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:27,800
Do you know where Mikoy
and Grandmother Ikay are?

30
00:01:27,867 --> 00:01:30,000
Grandmother Ikay
is in the capitol

31
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:32,967
but I don't know where Mikoy is.

32
00:01:34,567 --> 00:01:35,800
Okay. Thank you.

33
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:38,933
Of course,
the first prize winner

34
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:43,767
is no other than
the Eatery Queen,

35
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:47,233
it's Grandmother Ikay!

36
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:49,933
Congratulations!

37
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,767
- That was very delicious.
- Congratulations,

38
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:53,933
Grandmother Ikay.

39
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,633
- I told you.
- Grandmother.

40
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:58,433
- Oh my...
- I told you, you would win.

41
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,967
- This is beautiful.
- Yes.

42
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:01,567
Another trophy for you.

43
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,033
Mikoy.

44
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,100
Hazel?

45
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:08,000
Grandmother Ikay, hello.

46
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,367
Congratulations.

47
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:12,333
Thank you.

48
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,433
Hi.

49
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,533
I'm Hazel.

50
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,467
I'm Mikoy's girlfriend.

51
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:23,400
Is that how you will welcome me?

52
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:25,967
What I mean
is what are you doing here?

53
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:28,467
Well, I wanted to surprise you.

54
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:32,433
It was so foolish of me to think
that there's a better life

55
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,533
waiting for me in America

56
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:38,533
when all I ever need
is right here, with you.

57
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:42,500
So here I am, asking you
if we can start again.

58
00:02:43,967 --> 00:02:45,367
Can you give us another chance?

59
00:02:59,667 --> 00:03:01,333
Cuz, she's Hazel.

60
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:04,200
Who?

61
00:03:06,533 --> 00:03:07,500
As if you didn't hear me.

62
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:09,300
I said it's Hazel.

63
00:03:09,367 --> 00:03:11,200
Hazel is the name of the one
who hugged Mikoy.

64
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,800
Dear, I don't really need
to know.

65
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:16,167
The truth is I don't care.

66
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:17,700
You know,
it's none of my business.

67
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:21,300
Even if they kiss passionately,
I don't care.

68
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,167
Oh!

69
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:28,333
So you don't have to know
that she's Mikoy's girlfriend.

70
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:33,900
But they parted ways because
she needs to study in the US.

71
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,467
But I have a feeling
she's done with her studies,

72
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:43,900
that's why she's back
to reclaim what she owns.

73
00:03:47,033 --> 00:03:51,633
And I have a feeling they can
easily get back together.

74
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,167
Because after all,

75
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:57,600
Mikoy owes a huge amount
of gratitude to that woman.

76
00:03:57,700 --> 00:03:59,767
She's just the woman

77
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:04,867
who fixed the pieces
of Mikoy's heart

78
00:04:04,933 --> 00:04:11,667
when it was shattered
by his beloved Fashionista.

79
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:13,833
May-May, that's enough.

80
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:19,500
Celeste, thank you
for what you did.

81
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:21,500
You're welcome,
Grandmother Ikay.

82
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:24,333
You don't have to thank me
because it's about time

83
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:27,133
that the whole world
recognizes your talent.

84
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:31,200
I'm sure after this,
you will have new opportunities.

85
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:34,367
Are you okay, Celeste?

86
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:39,233
Of course, I'm more than okay.

87
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:25,167
No, unacceptable.

88
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:30,133
You know, it was supposed to be
Grandmother Ikay's event,

89
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,167
her cooking.

90
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:32,467
Then suddenly,

91
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,533
their public display
of affection was too much.

92
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:37,933
It's disgusting.
The truth is it's gross.

93
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,767
You know, honestly,
I was really surprised

94
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:43,633
that Mikoy had a history
with that woman.

95
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,667
But even before,

96
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:49,133
his taste is already a bit
doubtful when it comes to women.

97
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:52,300
Wait, aren't we talking
about your former boyfriend?

98
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,467
That's the thing.
I was also surprised

99
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,867
why I fell for him back then.

100
00:05:57,933 --> 00:06:00,800
Dear, I think
you're overreacting.

101
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:01,900
I'm overreacting?

102
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:04,000
I don't overreact.

103
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:05,967
I'm just protecting
Grandmother Ikay

104
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,533
because it was supposed to be
about her.

105
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,500
And they made it about them.

106
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,567
That woman
is really something else.

107
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:13,467
Why would I let her affect me?

108
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:14,867
That's the thing.

109
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:17,967
That's it. I gave her 30 minutes
on this phone call

110
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:19,333
so that's okay.

111
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,900
Anyway, I did what I needed
to do for Grandmother Ikay.

112
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:26,000
Now, if Mikoy wants to ruin
that, it's up to him.

113
00:06:26,067 --> 00:06:27,667
Right? Okay, goodbye.

114
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:34,967
I thought we will talk
about her designs.

115
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:37,733
She didn't tell me
that it's an angst moment.

116
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,667
I should've also prepared issues
about my ex.

117
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:42,767
Oh my...

118
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,200
I gave her 40 minutes.

119
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:07,133
Slowly, it's still hot.

120
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:11,833
What? Is it okay?

121
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,300
- Is it delicious?
- I will eat a lot of rice.

122
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,667
Come on, let's eat.

123
00:07:17,733 --> 00:07:18,200
You can eat now.

124
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:20,267
I'll use this.

125
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:24,700
You should've invited Hazel.

126
00:07:27,233 --> 00:07:29,433
I invited her but she needs
to go home.

127
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,533
There's also a welcome dinner
for her in their house.

128
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,667
Is that so?

129
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:33,033
Yes.

130
00:07:34,367 --> 00:07:37,333
How long will she stay here?

131
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,033
Is she here for vacation?

132
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,800
She will not go back to America
again.

133
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:44,867
She's staying for good.

134
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:47,400
- Really?
- Yes.

135
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:55,933
Does it mean
that you will get back together?

136
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,733
You know Grandmother,
I think there's nothing wrong

137
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,967
if we try to start again.

138
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:05,600
Hazel and I parted ways properly
back then.

139
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,867
We shared
a lot of good memories.

140
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:10,200
She never gave up on me.

141
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:15,267
The truth is, I should be happy
that she came back here.

142
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,300
Not only for herself,
but also for me.

143
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,200
Are you sure about that?

144
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:23,633
Yes, of course.

145
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:26,233
Hazel is a good person.

146
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:29,467
I'll be lucky if she becomes
a part of my life again.

147
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:34,700
What's important is she promises
to be with me

148
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:36,500
in the life that I chose
here in Sorsogon.

149
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,900
She chooses the life I chose.

150
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,867
James, don't just go.

151
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:00,267
Can you and Tiff talk first?

152
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,067
You should fix your problem.

153
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,933
I've had enough of her.

154
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,067
She's like that.

155
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:07,200
She treats everyone like that.

156
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,533
We're like trash.

157
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:13,267
If I were you, do something.

158
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:16,333
I'm not going back to her.

159
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,733
Does she think this is over?

160
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,100
She's wrong.

161
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,467
We're not yet done.

162
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,367
She'll see.

163
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,967
I will make her feel everything
that she made me feel.

164
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:41,333
What does he think of himself?

165
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,600
That he's God's gift to women?

166
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,133
And I'm crazy about him?

167
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:45,767
No way!

168
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:58,500
I knew it.

169
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:00,033
He will come back.

170
00:10:07,867 --> 00:10:08,367
Why?

171
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:11,067
Are you expecting someone else?

172
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,000
Is it James?

173
00:10:16,967 --> 00:10:18,833
I'm not in a good mood, Basti.

174
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,500
What do you want?
What do you need?

175
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:22,467
Well...

176
00:10:24,067 --> 00:10:26,067
I just want you to taste
my mother's cooking.

177
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:29,167
But you're not in the mood,

178
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,333
that's okay.

179
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,100
I'll just leave.

180
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:33,767
Wait.

181
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:39,967
You can come in.

182
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:53,000
So you think Aurelia
is being desperate?

183
00:10:56,433 --> 00:10:59,867
I'm not saying that
but ever since I announced

184
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:01,333
that Celeste and I
are getting married,

185
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:05,133
I get a certain kind
of aggressiveness with her.

186
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,300
And why do you think

187
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,467
you get that kind of vibe
from her?

188
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:12,733
I don't know.

189
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:16,600
You don't know?

190
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,067
Or you just don't want to say?

191
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,567
You're a smart man, Tonito.

192
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,067
And I think you have already
figured it out

193
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:28,867
why Aurelia is acting that way
towards you.

194
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,233
It was clear to her

195
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,267
that it's Celeste I love.

196
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,667
Are you sure?

197
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:38,167
Yes.

198
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:39,867
How about with Celeste?

199
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,033
Are you sure?

200
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:45,267
What do you mean?

201
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,900
Say whatever you want
when it comes to Aurelia,

202
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:53,700
but with her, what you see
is what you get.

203
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:56,133
How about with Celeste?

204
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:00,567
You know,
I don't want to speculate.

205
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:05,233
But honestly, everything
that Celeste shows me

206
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,600
doesn't seem to be true.

207
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,367
Up to this day,
she is a mystery to me.

208
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:15,367
A mystery that I cannot trust.

209
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,567
Maybe that's the reason

210
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:24,033
why Aurelia
is being aggressive with you.

211
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:29,867
She wants you back
because she wants to protect you

212
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:33,333
from a woman we can't trust.

213
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:49,167
Tonito...

214
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,900
Tonito, wait!

215
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:53,167
Toni...

216
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,267
Tonito, wait.

217
00:12:58,333 --> 00:12:58,733
Tonito!

218
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:00,333
Please.

219
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:03,267
What?

220
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,333
Is this part of your plan?

221
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:09,633
Are you and my sister
working together on this?

222
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:12,267
Tonito, calm down.

223
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,267
I just want to talk to you.

224
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,100
What for?

225
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,200
To apologize.

226
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:26,333
I realized I was out of line
these past few times.

227
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:31,200
Clearly, I was intruding
into your personal space.

228
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:33,833
I made trouble.

229
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:37,500
I'm adding destruction
into your life.

230
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,367
To be honest,

231
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:44,767
I'm being stupid for you.

232
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,633
- Aurelia...
- It's true!

233
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,333
That's really the truth.

234
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:55,833
Do you want honesty?

235
00:13:58,733 --> 00:13:59,833
I harbored this hope...

236
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:03,033
that we can still get back
together.

237
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,600
That there will come a time

238
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:08,800
that our family
will be whole again.

239
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,300
You,

240
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:12,733
me...

241
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:14,933
and Tiffany.

242
00:14:18,033 --> 00:14:21,333
But when you said that
you're going to marry Celeste,

243
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:23,867
I panicked.

244
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,167
And add to that the negative
reaction of Tiffany.

245
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,633
I felt like such a failure.

246
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:35,333
I failed being a wife.

247
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,200
I failed being a mother.

248
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:40,800
I wasn't able to keep our family
together.

249
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:46,700
But I realized...

250
00:14:49,633 --> 00:14:51,200
I cannot force things

251
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:56,700
just because they are not
aligned with my expectations.

252
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,200
I will only hurt you.

253
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:05,500
I will only hurt myself...

254
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,400
and the more I will only hurt
Tiffany.

255
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,267
I realized all that.

256
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,667
That's why I'm here...

257
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:21,633
apologizing.

258
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,467
Can we have dinner?

259
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:34,733
One last dinner...

260
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:36,833
for closure.

261
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:41,567
So once and for all,

262
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:44,700
we can move on...

263
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:50,367
with the lives
that we chose for each other.

264
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:54,800
Please?

265
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:17,933
There you go.

266
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,433
Thank you.

267
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,200
Oh my gosh, it's delicious.

268
00:16:34,267 --> 00:16:34,800
What is this?

269
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,667
Stewed frog legs.

270
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:41,067
What? Really?

271
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:42,267
- No. Oh my...
- No. Just a joke.

272
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,567
That's my mother's recipe.

273
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:49,433
It's chicken soup using papaya
instead of chayote.

274
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:51,567
Oh...

275
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:53,733
it's nice.

276
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,033
Basti...

277
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,100
thank you.

278
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:08,733
You came here just in time
because...

279
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:12,533
I'm a bit pissed today.

280
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:19,400
Well, Tiffany, the last time
we talked on the phone,

281
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:22,500
I felt that you and James
are not okay.

282
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:26,300
I'll talk to him, man to man.

283
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:30,433
To tell him it's only work,
nothing personal.

284
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:35,667
There's no need.

285
00:17:35,733 --> 00:17:38,333
But Tiffany,
I don't want to offend him.

286
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:40,467
That's not my style.

287
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,067
I'll talk to him
to clear everything.

288
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,767
There's no need
because he's gone.

289
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,200
He's gone?

290
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:55,100
As in he's dead?

291
00:17:56,167 --> 00:17:57,667
When? What happened to him?

292
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:59,267
Basti... Basti, chill.

293
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:00,000
Don't overreact.

294
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:05,533
What I only mean is...

295
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:10,567
we broke up.

296
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:25,900
James and I are not like this.

297
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:29,633
In almost a year
that we've been together,

298
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,567
sometimes he loves me,

299
00:18:31,633 --> 00:18:32,533
sometimes not.

300
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:40,333
Sometimes he makes me
feel special...

301
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:43,033
but most of the time,
he doesn't.

302
00:18:49,867 --> 00:18:51,500
His ego is so high.

303
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,300
He's so full of pride.

304
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:00,900
He only thinks about himself.

305
00:19:04,133 --> 00:19:05,400
He's so arrogant.

306
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,500
He's so entitled.

307
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:11,633
He's possessive and he feels
that he owns me.

308
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,800
You can see it, right?

309
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:19,767
But you still love him?

310
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:22,500
I don't know.

311
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,133
I don't know.

312
00:19:30,367 --> 00:19:32,267
But I shouldn't, right?

313
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:37,967
I don't know.

314
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:44,200
But Clau...

315
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:50,633
every time I think
of how he treated me

316
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,633
and how he treats me right now,

317
00:19:54,633 --> 00:19:56,333
I'm pissed with myself.

318
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:01,600
I feel stupid because I know
I don't deserve that.

319
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,733
What if he comes back?

320
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,633
What if he tries
to win you back?

321
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,933
You are like that, right?

322
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,667
On and off, on and off.

323
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,833
Tiff, we both know James.

324
00:20:21,567 --> 00:20:24,567
He goes away
but he always comes back.

325
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,933
Give our regards
to your mom and dad.

326
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,900
Yes, Hazel,
it's been a long time

327
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:45,333
they haven't visited Sorsogon.

328
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,900
They are busy.

329
00:20:47,967 --> 00:20:51,567
I hope I can also go to America
like you, Hazel.

330
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:55,067
I'm not sure
if that's a good idea, Basti.

331
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:57,333
Nowadays, if you are in America

332
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,300
and you are walking
on the street,

333
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,000
the Americans
will attack you.

334
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:04,067
- That's right.
- I heard about that.

335
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:07,300
That's why for me
#StopAsianHate.

336
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:10,000
Was that the reason
you came home?

337
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:12,267
It's one of the many reasons.

338
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:16,967
But the real reason

339
00:21:17,033 --> 00:21:19,433
is I really want to build a life
here.

340
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,367
Like Mikoy,

341
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:25,700
I want to use a little
of what I learned abroad

342
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:27,900
to help in the development
of the community.

343
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:28,633
That's nice.

344
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:30,700
That's good.

345
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:36,667
Good morning.

346
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,000
We have a visitor.

347
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,600
To what do I owe you
the pleasure?

348
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:14,433
Good morning, Mikoy!

349
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:16,733
Good morning, May.
Why are you here so early?

350
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:22,467
Nothing, I just want to know
what's going on.

351
00:22:25,733 --> 00:22:26,667
What do you need?

352
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,333
I just want to ask if...

353
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,800
you and Celeste have no
community service for today?

354
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:36,967
None because it's weekend today.

355
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:41,733
So she can also rest and attend
to her fashion business.

356
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:47,900
Is that so?

357
00:22:49,667 --> 00:22:50,533
You're irritating.

358
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:52,867
Why? What do you want?

359
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:53,633
What do you want to say?

360
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:55,067
Nothing.

361
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:58,167
You know make yourself useful.

362
00:22:58,233 --> 00:22:59,300
You should help me

363
00:22:59,367 --> 00:23:00,433
so when Grandmother Ikay
comes home,

364
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:01,000
this is already okay.

365
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:06,667
By the way, I came
from Uncle Patricio's house.

366
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:08,300
They have a visitor.

367
00:23:09,967 --> 00:23:10,433
Who?

368
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:12,633
It's Hazel.

369
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:18,767
Hazel? What is she doing there?

370
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:20,533
I have no idea.

371
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:25,333
But I feel
there will be a cockfight.

372
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:09,067
Basti, aren't we supposed
to set up today?

373
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:11,167
There's a sudden event here
at home.

374
00:24:11,233 --> 00:24:13,667
It looks like a big cockfight
is going to take place.

375
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,167
Did you replace me
with a cockfight?

376
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:16,933
Actually, that's what's good
about Hazel.

377
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,833
She is very supportive
of everything I do

378
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:21,600
- here in the province.
- So she will stay here?

379
00:24:21,667 --> 00:24:23,833
She's not going back to the US?

380
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:26,233
There's nothing wrong if the two
of you will have closure.

381
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,500
Do you exactly believe

382
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:29,267
that Aurelia is the type
of person

383
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:32,000
who can give closure
without anything in return?

384
00:24:32,067 --> 00:24:34,833
Celeste is just a detour
for Tonito.

385
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,367
Ultimately, it's still the two
of us in the end.

386
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,533
Tiffany?

387
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:43,400
I knew it. Just one look
at that woman,

388
00:24:43,467 --> 00:24:45,233
I know I can't trust her.

389
00:24:45,300 --> 00:24:50,167
I can see right through her
and I know she's not sincere.

390
00:24:50,233 --> 00:24:52,267
This is my chance
to reveal to everyone

391
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:54,000
how little her brain is.

392
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:54,867
What do you think?
